db/alembic — Alembic env + versions

This is the Alembic-managed schema migration infrastructure. It supersedes
the raw SQL files in `db/migrations/_archived/` (which were the canonical
migration path through 2026-07-19, migration 0021).

How it works:

- `env.py` loads the workspace src/ paths, points Alembic at
  `constat_api.orm.Base.metadata` (single source of truth), and reads
  the DB URL from `constat_api.settings` (the same `CONSTAT_DATABASE_URL`
  env var the API uses).
- `versions/` is the chain of revisions. The first revision (baseline) is
  a no-op that anchors the chain at the schema produced by SQL
  migrations 0001..0021.
- `script.py.mako` is the stock revision template; autogenerate fills it
  in based on ORM ↔ DB diff.

Bootstrap (AGENTS.md dev section): `uv run alembic -c db/alembic.ini
upgrade head` from the workspace root. CI uses the same command against
its service-container Postgres.

See ADR-17 for the rationale (baseline, no re-issue of historical
revisions, autogenerate from ORM going forward).
